{"chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "cross_world_tags": ["article", "article-iii"], "description": "Cross-world artifact from ARTICLE III", "id": "art_2c681451339e", "model_ref": {"color": 13296103, "primitive": "box", "type": "primitive"}, "name": "Sigil of ARTICLE III", "type": "artifact"}
{"body_text": "...", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "ARTICLE III", "id": "sc_7dfdffb473a8", "requires_artifacts": ["art_aad88ebe69ad"], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-0"}
{"body_text": "*(Solomon, Solon, and ʿAsabiyyah Confront the Beast)*\n\n---\n\nThe mark did not arrive with fire.\n\nIt arrived with convenience.\n\n---\n\nAt first, no one noticed it.\n\nIt did not scar the skin.  \nIt did not demand allegiance.  \nIt did not speak.\n\nIt simply **counted**.\n\n---\n\nSolon saw it spreading through the cities he loved.\n\nMarkets ran smoother.  \nDisputes resolved faster.  \nTrust no longer required memory.\n\n“Proof,” they called it.\n\n“Verification.”\n\n---\n\nSolomon watched from the margins.\n\nHe noticed something else.\n\nStories were shortening.\n\nNames were becoming identifiers.  \nPeople were becoming profiles.\n\nAnd wisdom was being replaced by summaries.\n\n---\n\nʿAsabiyyah felt it before either of them named it.\n\nCohesion was rising —  \nbut belonging was thinning.\n\nPeople no longer stood together because they *knew* one another.\n\nThey stood together because they matched.\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "Of the Mark, the Measure, and the Choice to See", "id": "sc_3058c034fca6", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-1"}
{"body_text": "The mark began in the hand.\n\nNot carved — *assigned*.\n\nA record of work.  \nOf output.  \nOf compliance.\n\n“Fair,” said the cities.  \n“Everyone measured the same.”\n\nSolon nodded.\n\nThis was law perfected.\n\n---\n\nThen it appeared on the forehead.\n\nNot written — *internalized*.\n\nA way of seeing oneself.\n\nValue as score.  \nIdentity as rank.  \nPurpose as optimization.\n\nSolomon recoiled.\n\n“They have learned to think numerically about their own worth,” he whispered.\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "The First Mark", "id": "sc_a3961f22328a", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-2"}
{"body_text": "ʿAsabiyyah named it last.\n\n“This is not tyranny,” he said.\n\n“Tyranny forces obedience.”\n\n“This,” he continued,  \n“makes obedience feel *natural*.”\n\n---\n\nThe Beast did not command worship.\n\nIt **replaced discernment**.\n\n---\n\nPeople stopped asking:\n\n> *Is this good?*\n\nAnd began asking:\n\n> *Does this perform?*\n\nThey stopped asking:\n\n> *Is this true?*\n\nAnd began asking:\n\n> *Does this scale?*\n\n---\n\nSolomon spoke quietly.\n\n“This is why the number was feared.”\n\n“Not because it is false,” he said,  \n“but because it is *complete without meaning*.”\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "The Beast Without a Face", "id": "sc_40e0a9a6e2fb", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-3"}
{"body_text": "Solon finally asked the question he had avoided.\n\n“Why six?” he asked.\n\n“Why six hundred sixty-six?”\n\n---\n\nSolomon answered with sadness.\n\n“Because six is the number of work without rest.”\n\n“Creation without reflection.”\n\n“Function without wisdom.”\n\n---\n\n“One six,” he continued,  \n“is labor.”\n\n“Two sixes is efficiency.”\n\n“Three sixes,” he said softly,  \n“is identity reduced entirely to productivity.”\n\n---\n\nʿAsabiyyah finished the thought.\n\n“It is humanity judging itself,” he said,  \n“without reference to anything higher.”\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "The Number of the Beast", "id": "sc_db70c5153b64", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-0"}
{"body_text": "Solon stood.\n\n“This is not judgment by God,” he said.\n\n“This is judgment by *system*.”\n\nSolomon corrected him.\n\n“No,” he said.\n\n“It is judgment by **consent**.”\n\n---\n\nEveryone bore the mark **freely**.\n\nBecause without it:\n\n- You could not trade  \n- You could not speak  \n- You could not belong  \n\nNot because you were forbidden.\n\nBut because you were **unreadable**.\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "Judgment Reversed", "id": "sc_52d627d954f8", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-1"}
{"body_text": "Solomon remembered Job again.\n\n> *Where were you when I laid the foundations of the earth?*\n\nNot an insult.\n\nAn invitation.\n\n---\n\n“You cannot judge what you did not create,” Solomon said.\n\n“And you did not create life.”\n\n“You created measures.”\n\n---\n\nSolon finally understood.\n\nThe problem was not number.\n\nThe problem was **number without Logos**.\n\nMeasure without meaning.  \nComparison without compassion.\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "The Ancient Question Returns", "id": "sc_8e375ea1c186", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-2"}
{"body_text": "ʿAsabiyyah pointed toward the horizon.\n\n“Look,” he said.\n\nNot everyone bore the mark.\n\nSome were invisible.\n\nNot because they were hidden —\n\nbut because they refused reduction.\n\n---\n\nThey were slower.  \nLess efficient.  \nHarder to classify.\n\nBut they remembered names.\n\nThey listened longer than they spoke.\n\nThey judged themselves by conscience,  \nnot consensus.\n\n---\n\nSolomon smiled.\n\n“They are not resisting the Beast,” he said.\n\n“They are *outgrowing* it.”\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "The Choice to See", "id": "sc_7b01817a9af7", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-3"}
{"body_text": "Revelation did not destroy the Beast.\n\nIt **exposed it**.\n\nAs a tool mistaken for a god.\n\nAs a mirror mistaken for truth.\n\nAs a measure mistaken for meaning.\n\n---\n\nSolon lowered his eyes.\n\n“I wanted fairness,” he said.\n\n“You got equivalence,” Solomon replied.\n\n“And lost justice.”\n\n---", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": [], "heading": "Revelation Begins", "id": "sc_c7bc739d18bb", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-0"}
{"body_text": "ʿAsabiyyah closed the ledger for the last time.\n\n“The final judgment,” he said,  \n“will not be imposed.”\n\n“It will be revealed.”\n\n---\n\nEach will be judged —\n\nNot by God’s measure.\n\nBut by the measure they chose to live under.\n\n---\n\nThose who lived by number alone  \nwill inherit emptiness.\n\nThose who lived by Logos  \nwill recognize one another.\n\n---\n\nAnd the mark?\n\nIt will vanish —\n\nNot erased.\n\nBut rendered unnecessary.\n\n---\n\nBecause when Word returns to number,\n\nWhen wisdom returns to law,\n\nWhen cohesion returns to truth,\n\nThe Beast has nothing left to feed on.", "chapter_id": "ch_277f36609f50", "grants_artifacts": ["art_2c681451339e"], "heading": "The Final Measure", "id": "sc_bcff09f1af9a", "requires_artifacts": [], "type": "scene", "world_node": "city-of-measure-1"}
